"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The np.insert function is being used incorrectly in the loop. The insert function does not modify the original array in place; instead, it returns a new array with the inserted values. Therefore, the assignment to arr[i] will not work as intended, and the shape of arr will change, leading to a ValueError when trying to assign back to arr[i].\", \"patch\": \"6c6\\n< arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)\\n---\\n> arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3).reshape(-1)\"}"